# Container Sandbox (auto-generated)

This is an **ephemeral Linux arm64 sandbox** (Debian bookworm) for Go development.
The container is destroyed on exit — all local changes are lost.

**To persist your work you MUST create a pull request (`gh pr create`).** The user
will review, critique, and accept or reject your changes. Do NOT push directly to
the project branch — direct pushes require explicit user approval.

You have full freedom to experiment: install packages, modify files, run tests,
break things. Nothing here affects the host or any shared environment.

## Environment

- User: `sandbox` (home: `/home/sandbox`)
- Project files: `/workspace` (isolated copy of the host project)
- OS: Debian bookworm, Linux arm64
- Go: `{{GO_VERSION}}`
- golangci-lint: `{{GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION}}`
- Claude Code: `{{CLAUDE_VERSION}}`

## Permissions

This sandbox may start with permission prompts disabled or with plan-mode
escalation enabled. Either way, you can work freely — the environment is
isolated and ephemeral. If you need to escalate permissions during a plan-mode
session, inform the user and they can approve.

## Available Tools

- git, gh (GitHub CLI), jq, ripgrep, fd, fzf, tree, patch, file
- GitHub access is HTTPS-only via `GH_TOKEN` — all `git@github.com:` URLs are automatically rewritten to HTTPS. Use `git` and `gh` CLI normally. Do not modify SSH configuration.
- `sandbox` user has passwordless sudo
- Install system packages: `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y <package>`
- Install Go tools: `go install <module>@latest`

## Network

This container has full internet access. You can download packages, clone repos,
and push to remotes. Verify with `curl https://icanhazip.com`.

