### Building

Build binaries to the project `bin/` directory:

```bash
go build -o ./bin/ ./...
```

All compiled binaries are Linux arm64 — they will not run on macOS.

### Recommended workflow

```bash
goimports -w .
golangci-lint run ./...
gotestsum -- -race ./...
govulncheck ./...
```

<if HAS_CODEX>
## Codex CLI

Codex CLI is installed and registered as an MCP server (`codex`).
It provides tools via `codex mcp-server`. Auth uses ChatGPT OAuth
(credentials copied from host `~/.codex/`). Config: `~/.codex/config.toml`.

Use `codex` for code generation, refactoring, and analysis. Treat `codex` as your pair programmer.
When Write or Edit tools are blocked use `codex` for code generation and refactoring.
Give `codex` detailed instructions, verify its output. Keep delta small.

**IMPORTANT — Codex sandbox mode:** You are running inside an isolated Apple
Container. Codex has its own Landlock sandbox which is redundant here and blocks
filesystem access. When calling Codex MCP tools, you MUST always pass
`sandbox: "danger-full-access"` and `approval-policy: "never"`.

Example:

```
codex(prompt: "your prompt here", cwd: "/workspace", sandbox: "danger-full-access", approval-policy: "never")
```

Without these parameters Codex defaults to `read-only` and cannot access files.
</if>
